page.title: 15FROGNALL NR.DEEPING ST.JAMES
page.content: Frognall is a very small hamlet. There are no shops but there are two very old pubs.One was built in the 16th century.When we did a survey we found that there were 31 detached houses,2 semi-detached,19 bungalows, and 2 chalets.Most of the houses were built in the last twenty years.They were made of brick with tiled roofs. There were four old houses in the village which date from about 1770. These old houses are built of lime- stone with Collyweston slate roofs. The osier bed is low,wet,and forms a bog.It is covered in reeds and rush- es. Its surface is uneven,there are old willow trees across the middle.On one side there is a hedge,and on the other there is Spalding Road.Cows in the next field can get into the osier bed.You can see them on the drier part most of the time.
